        "id": 2410264,
        "name": "Dennis Atick",
        "username": "Dennis_Atick",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_atick/{size}/429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-05-06T20:13:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Very good stuff right here.</p>\n<p>[*]<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2212923&amp;iNote=7013161\"><strong>2014 Domaine Pattes Loup Chablis 1er Cru Beauregard</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, Chablis, Chablis 1er Cru (5/6/2018)</em><br>\nTerrific young Chablis from Thomas Pico. The aromatics are initially reticent, takes some airing out. The wine feels wound up, but slowly reveals a vibrant energy with citrus fruit, richness on the palate that is buffered by crisp acidity that enlivens everything. Rally pops. A salinity comes forward on the finish that sails on leaving an impression. Excellent young Chablis that I want to see again in 3 years and more.<br>\n<em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T04:20:28.275Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
