        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"William Kelley\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n William Kelley:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Couldn\u2019t agree more!</p>\n<p>Thomas left some 2015 Butteaux on the lees in tank for over two years which I think he has bottled now, that\u2019s a fun wine to track down.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p><img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\" class=\"animated\"></p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"John Ammons\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n John Ammons:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Had the 2012 version of this wine last night.  It was splendid as well.  In fact, other than nothing being reticent upon opening, it fit the above description nicely. The 2012 was reading to roll out the gate.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Good to know. This is a new house to me. Honestly, David Beuker\u2019s recent notes sent me searching for some. Really compelling stuff.</p>",
